name: Maison Simba
address: Jalan Pantai Kedungu No.7 PACUNG, BELALLANG, Belalang, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
Beautiful and luxury colonial guest house! I was staying there for the weekend and there is no word to describe this place... An amazing experience in a great decor and comfy Singaporean house. Located in a charming area between ricefields and jungle, Maison Simba is composed by 3 Indonesian styling rooms decorated with passion (antic art pieces and modern style from travels around the world) and 1 rustic Joglo, traditional house.
Friendly staff, homemade and delicious fresh food, comfy living rooms and plunge pool... Enjoy your stay and let's share a dining time with Antoine, owner and interior designer.
I recommend this place to anyone wants to take some rest for few days and enjoy the surroundings of Tabanan in a refined atmosphere!
review 2:
This is a magnificient colonial "Maison" in absolut calm , succulent dished, with a sublime swimming-pool.
The universe of the house will enchant you with its smells selected with choice by owner. Every object was carefully selected and the white & blue living room is a beauty.
I encourage everyone to enjoy a stay at this house, where you will feel at home, and discuss with the owner that will make you come back to another time!
review 3:
What a place to stay!! Relaxing, hidden and offering phenomenal food from breakfast to dinner.
Thanks to Eric and all his crew who make us have an unforgettable moment at MaisonSimba
review 4: A stunning Singapore colonial house tucked in the wilderness near Thana Lot. Host is a renowned interior designer with exquisite taste. A wonderfully stylish retreat.
review 5: Beautiful Singaporean black and white house in Bali!
